6. HOW WE SHARE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION  
We may share your personal information with the following people at present:  
 the Scheme employers and members of the employers' group of companies;  
 the Scheme administrator s; 
 any new trustees or trustee directors of any corporate trustee;  
 auditors;  
 the Revenue Commissioners;  
 the Data Protection Commissioner;  
 IT and data storage providers;  
 authorised b rokers;  
 actuarial advisers;  
 your r elatives or legal personal representatives (where necessary to provide benefits in the event of 
your death) ; 
 other support service providers and adv isers necessary to support the Trustees in the 
administration of the  Scheme  (including printers ); 
 other regulatory bodies to whom we are obliged or required to disclose your personal information.  
 our  professional advisers  (including lawyers, actuaries and medical practitioners) ; 
 insurers and life assurance companies;  
 the Pensions Authority;  
 the Financial Services and Pensions Ombudsman's Bureau of Ireland ; and  
 the Workplace Relations Commission, Courts, Court appointed persons.  
In certain circumstances we will also need to provide the administrators and trustees of other pension 
arrangements with personal information about you (for example, where your benefits are transferred to such 
other arrangement  and for the purpose  of calculating any benefits payable to or in respect of you). We also 
share your personal information with the Scheme’s employers also so they can contact you about your 
benefits under the Scheme, and any additional options which may be available to you i n relation to those 
benefits.   
We may also share your personal information with someone else where you have given your consent – for 
example, where you transfer your benefits out of the Scheme.  
Further details of the Scheme's advisers are contained in th e Trustee Annual Report.  If you would like any 
further information regarding the persons with whom your information is shared please contact us using the 
